    "text": "Respiratory rate is just how many breaths you take per minute while you sleep. Last night's 16.8 isn't a red flag by your own history: it sits about 0.6 above your 30-day baseline of 16.2, well inside your normal night-to-night wiggle. Your 7-day average is 16.4, so there's no sustained climb here either — this is one slightly high night. Two honest caveats: this value is sensor-estimated from the wrist, so small moves are approximate, and a fixed internet cutoff is a population rule of thumb, not a measurement of you. The pattern that would actually deserve attention is a rise sustained across several nights alongside feeling run-down — and your data doesn't show that.",
